{
  "texts": [
    "These challenges stem from the inherent limitations of LLMs in grounding language to real-world physics and the computational overhead of traditional KGs.",
    "Our work addresses these gaps by integrating Embodied Robotic Control Prompts (ERCPs) for instruction refinement, an Embodied Knowledge Graph (EKG) for structured environmental representation, and algorithmic optimizations (GATs, Hamiltonian Paths) to prioritize safety-critical constraints.",
    "Embodied Robotic Control Prompt (ERCP)The Embodied Robotic Control Prompt (ERCP) framework provides a structured mechanism for guiding Large Language Models (LLMs) to clarify ambiguous or incomplete human instructions through iterative refinement.",
    "The ERCP framework coordinates the interaction between the user, the LLM, and the robotic system to ensure the generation of safe and precise task plans.",
    "These plans adhere to spatial relationships, action sequences, safety constraints, and performance metrics, while dynamically resolving ambiguities in natural language instructions.1) LLM Integration in the ERCP Workflow: The ERCP leverages the LLM for the following key operations:1) Analyzing Instructions: The LLM identifies ambiguities, missing details, or inconsistencies in the user's instruction (e.g., \"Bring me a drink\")."
  ]
}